-- Exxon, Sabic Choose HSBC to Advise on $5 Billion Deal, MEED Says
-- B y   A y e s h a   D a y a
-- 2011-12-19T11:13:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-19/exxon-sabic-choose-hsbc-to-advise-on-5-billion-deal-meed-says.html
Exxon Mobil Corp. (XOM)  and  Saudi Basic
Industries Corp. (SABIC)  appointed  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  to advise on a $5
billion elastomers project at Jubail in Saudi Arabia, Middle
East Economic Digest reported, citing unidentified bankers.  Banks will be approached in late 2012 to fund the project,
which will produce more than 400,000 tons of rubber among other
products, according to the publication.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ayesha Daya in Dubai at 
 adaya1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
